Since I don't think you get it, I react badly when people label Non-Sentai Toku as power rangers.

Since I'm feeling generous today, I'll just give a really boring history lesson.

!http://fc01.deviantart.net/fs70/i/2012/350/3/4/kamen_rider_ichigo_by_yorkemaster-d5o9ial.jpg!
In early 1971, Shotaro ishinomori created Masked Rider (Also known as Kamen rider) It's basically about a Man who becomes an insect themed Motorcycle riding cyborg who uses his power to fight the forces of evil. It was a huge success, Starting the "Henshin boom" Which resulted in many sequels, And Other attempts at superhero shows. (Goranger also got many sequels, And would later get one of them adapted into power rangers)

It makes sense that 4 Random Shmucks with Superpowers suddenly granted woudn't be the greatest at fighting Beings that can twist the fabric of Space-time without much effort. (Red Hawk Is a military man, Blue Swallow is a High school girl, White swan is a rich girl, Yellow owl is a farmer, And black condor is a street fighter and a general thug.)

Also, The Jetman powers were all intended for military people, But after Red hawk got his powers, the Vyram attacked their Space base and the powers ended up going to those 4 on earth.
